common, router

### Description

Hello, 

I'm working on a Angular UI project where the entire app is a `customElement` ex `app-web-component`

The host UI would add the the `app-web-component` to a part of its page with URL like  `host/componentPage/componentView` and `componentView` is a route inside the `app-web-component`

When the user directly goes to `host/componentPage/componentView` I would like to have the `componentView` route shown in the UI 

I tried with the approach in the alternatives considered section
It works, but the way to configure the application seems a bit less than ideal
Instead I would like to pass the baseHref as a value in the component's attribute 
```html
<app-web-component 
   id="component" 
   baseHref="/host/application/componentRoute"
></app-web-component>
```

This is where I got stuck because because there doesn't seem to be a way to update `baseHref` to `APP_BASE_HREF`  from inside the `app.component.ts`

And the `Location` and `LocationStrategy` statically assign this as private variables
https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/main/packages/common/src/location/location.ts#L76
https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/main/packages/common/src/location/location_strategy.ts#L122 during construction so hard to change in ts code

### Proposed solution

Suggestion to add a feature in the `provideRouter` with something like `withDynamicBaseHref()` or `withCustomElementBaseHref()`

I created a hacky wrapper implementation of this using some of the internal API's in angular as a separate provider and felt that this could be a potential feature

Implementation: https://github.com/Rajendran-Balaji/angular-custom-element-routing/blob/main/src/app/dynamic-base-href.provider.ts 

If this feature is not considered, I have another suggestion 
To update the private `_baseHref`, `_basePath` variables 
to protected methods so that they could allow for simple class extends 
```
class LocationStrategy {
   protected  setBaseHref() {}

   protected  getBaseHref() {}

  override prepareExternalUrl(internal: string): string {
    return joinWithSlash(this.getBaseHref(), internal);
  }

}

class Location {
   protected  setBasePath() {}

   protected  setBasePath() {}

  normalize(url: string): string {
    return Location.stripTrailingSlash(_stripBasePath(this.getBasePath(), _stripIndexHtml(url)));
  }

}
```



