**Important:** with the normal build it works perfectly fine.

### Expected Behavior:

The builderMode: "application" and accompanying loader map should be accepted by the test builderâ€™s schema, enabling esbuild to inline or fileâ€emit .svg imports exactly as in the application build.

Specs importing SVGs should compile under the esbuildâ€powered pipeline without further WebPack tweaks.

[Docs to the implementation example](https://angular.dev/tools/cli/build-system-migration#file-extension-loader-customization)
[Docs to the test build](https://angular.dev/tools/cli/build-system-migration#new-features)

### Actual Behavior:

The CLI fails schema validation on angular.json with an error like:

```
Schema validation failed with the following errors:
  Data path â€œ/projects/phlu-webapp/architect/test/optionsâ€ should NOT have additional properties(loader).
```
Tests continue to use the WebPackâ€based Karma builder (which knows nothing about esbuild loaders), so importing an SVG in a spec throws:

`No loader is configured for ".svg" files`

